explanation: Convert string to mutable char array, then process in 2k-sized blocks. Reverse the first k characters of each block in-place with two-pointer swap. Handles edge cases (remaining < k or k ≤ remaining < 2k) by clamping the right pointer. Single pass, minimal extra memory.

